thread.Abort();

// âś… .NET 8 â€” cooperative cancellation
var cts = new CancellationTokenSource();
var task = Task.Run(() =>
{
    while (!cts.Token.IsCancellationRequested)
    {
        // do work
    }
}, cts.Token);

cts.Cancel();       // request cancellation
await task;         // wait for clean exit
```

**Summary:** Your code is safe to migrate directly. Replace `Thread` with `Task`/`Parallel` for modern patterns, and if you find `Thread.Abort` elsewhere, switch to `CancellationToken`.
